Package: causalontology
Type: Package
Title: R Binding of the Causalontology Standard
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: person("AI University (AIU)", email = "ai.university.aiu@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The R binding of the Causalontology standard (specification
    2.0.0, the whole-word re-mint of Principle P7): content-addressed
    identity over RFC 8785 (JSON Canonicalization Scheme) identity-bearing
    bytes with SHA-256, Ed25519 record-level signing and verification
    (RFC 8032), validation against the seventeen specification JSON Schemas
    (including cross-file schema references), the semantic rules and the
    five normative algorithms of Section 12 (bridge closure, bridged
    hierarchy reachability, stratal classification, the skip decision
    procedure, and unit normalization) plus the rule 13-21 helpers (bridge
    and conduit well-formedness, state value and unit coherence,
    covering-law and retrocausality checks, and graph acyclicity), and an
    in-memory conformant store with idempotent immutable puts, signed
    add-only provenance records with quarantine, materialized enrichment
    views with contributors, retraction and succession lineage, the resolve
    minimum, the deterministic cycle-breaking view rule, and the stigmergy
    gap read. Conformance is defined by the 107 vectors frozen at
    specification 2.0.0 in the standard's repository; run conformance.R
    against them. Crypto uses a pure-R SHA-256 plus the 'openssl' package
    for Ed25519 (RFC 8032).
License: Apache License 2.0 | file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    openssl (>= 1.4.1),
    stats,
    utils
